commit.message:
fix: validation check should handle zero values

validation check for defaults did not handle zero value for cpu quota
added unit tests to handle all stand alone default values

Signed-off-by: ehila <ehila@redhat.com>

oci: AttachContainer: always read attach socket

conmon uses blocking writes on attach socket, if we do not read at all,
conmon will be stuck.

Signed-off-by: Pinghao Wu <xdavidwuph@gmail.com>

commit.message:
upkeep: small wording changes

fixed wording mistakes and validation error wording
added explicit info for units on cpu period and cpu quotas

Signed-off-by: ehila <ehila@redhat.com>

feat: add support for cpu limits for workloads

Added the ability to support cpuquota and cpuperiod for specific
workloads, this allows more fine tune control for containers that are assigned
to those workloads to be set to a specific CPU quota.

Added a wrapper struct for annotation object to be used for information
such as cpu milli cores to be used in the calculation for cpu quota.

Signed-off-by: ehila <ehila@redhat.com>

commit.message:
Add dynamic pull timeout

We now support a pull context which can actually be cancelled. This way
we can combine the pull progress together with a dynamic timeout, which
cancels the context if no progress is being made on pull.

Signed-off-by: Sascha Grunert <sgrunert@redhat.com>

Add dynamic pull timeout

We now support a pull context which can actually be cancelled. This way
we can combine the pull progress together with a dynamic timeout, which
cancels the context if no progress is being made on pull.

Signed-off-by: Sascha Grunert <sgrunert@redhat.com>

commit.message:
packit: Update config and sync to Fedora

With this change:
- COPR builds are now run per-PR
- Packit will open PRs to the Fedora dist-git repo when a new release is created
- the `%global commit0` value is updated in the specfile for each build

Signed-off-by: Christian Glombek <cglombek@redhat.com>

In some cases the seccomp_notifier does not have time to stop
the workload, in that cases exit code of container is 0.

This PR change the checking way from exit code to status state.

Signed-off-by: roman-kiselenko <roman.kiselenko.dev@gmail.com>
